2016 metais žurnalisto Andriaus Tapino įkurta nepriklausoma, žiūrovų išlaikoma televizija per septynerius gyvavimo metus sukūrė daugiau nei tūkstantį įvairaus formato ir žanro laidų. 

Šiandien drąsiai sakome – mes ne tik televizija, todėl jungiamės į Laisvės Media Group šeimą ir vykdome daug prasmingų ir svarbių veiklų, išlipančių iš televizijos rėmų. Vienydami aktyvius, pilietiškus ir laisvus keisti žmones įgaliname vieni kitus kurti nepriklausomą ir kokybišką turinį, kelti visuomenei opias problemas ir aktyviai reaguojant į aktualijas inicijuoti visuomeninius projektus. Tokios mūsų iniciatyvos, kaip „Bayraktaras Ukrainai“, „Legion of Boom“, „Magyla“, „Laikykitės, medikai“, „Laisvės kelias“, „Viso gero, Valdemarai“, „Laisvė gyvūnams“, „Laikykitės, pasieniečiai“, „Skaidrinam“ ir kitos,  garsina Lietuvos vardą visame pasaulyje.

Laisvės Media Group šeimą sudaro: 

Laisvės TV – pelno nesiekianti ir pilietinę visuomenės švietimo misiją vykdanti televizija;
Laisvės TV X – pramoginis, jaunimo auditorijai skirtas antrasis „Laisvės TV“ kanalas;  
Laisvės TV komanda – tai profesionalai, turintys ilgametę patirtį media produkcijos gamybos ir transliavimo srityse.

Metacepthas been created with an objective of developing and sustaining a platform for a productive discussion on the ever-evolving fields of Information Technology [InfoTech] and Intellectual Property Rights [IPR] Laws. We aim at promoting a diversity of viewpoints, ideas, and ideologies. Metacept welcomes guest posts from students, academics, practitioners, early career researchers, policy-makers, and members of civil society organizations.

Guest Post Guidelines:

The post should contain a suitable and catchy title.
The post should be around 600-800 words [excluding footnotes];
We encourage contributors to mention keywords of their article below it;
Posts must include hyperlinks to relevant legal sources and background information;
Citation style must be uniform. [APA or Bluebook preferred];
Posts should be clear and concise, leaving out excessive jargon and verbiage;
Posts should not exceed 10% plagiarism; and
We encourage the writers to share the URL of their respective LinkedIn profile with us.

How to Submit

Contributors are expected to conform to the above guidelines and send the post as a .doc file to editor@metacept.com with the subject line as ‘Guest Post – Area [InfoTech or IPR]’
For any further query, feel free to write to us at info@metacept.com!

PROFIT system is a consulting firm specialized in franchise consultancy in Central and Eastern European countries (esp. Poland, Ukraine, Russia, Czech Republic, Slovakia, Hungary, Romania, Serbia, Croatia, Slovenia). We provide a wide range of services and products in the field of franchise business.

PROFIT system is a publisher of a franchise monthly magazine in Poland (wlasnybiznes.com) and quaterly  franchise magazines in Czech Republic (vlastnifirma.cz) and in Ukraine (ideibiznesa.com), and professional franchise portals in Poland (Franchising.pl), Ukrainie (Franchising.ua), Russia (FranchisingINFO.ru), Czech Republic (Franchising.cz), Slovakia (Franchising.sk), Hungary (Franchising.hu), Romania (Franchising.info.ro), Serbia (Franchising.rs), Croatia (Franchising.hr) and Slovenia (Franchising.si). 

The company was established in 1998. Since that time we we have been working for over 900 franchisers.

We offer:
* creation of business model for franchisers;
* drafting franchise agreement or adjusting existing one;
* preparation or adjustment of existing operations manual;
* recruitment of franchisees;
* marketing and public relations support for franchisers.

AgriPortal provides prompt, reliable and comprehensive information about what is happening on the markets of major cereals and oilseeds in Romania, the Balkans, Europe, the Black Sea region and the world.
Our mission is to become a starting point for making informed decisions about sales and risk management in the complex and volatile field of grain trade. 
Our focus is on the news and prices of milling wheat, feed wheat, corn, sunflower, rapeseed, barley, soybeans, as well as on their derivatives - meal, oils, DDGS, bran, etc.
Our subscribers can take full advantage of the features on AgriPortal platform:
•	Full range of quoted agri commodities futures on international exchanges in Paris (MATIF) and Chicago (CME / SWOT) in real time;
•	A large number of physical market prices for the most important commodities in the subsections "International Physical Markets", "Oils, meals and feed", "Beans, rice and organic" and "Fertilizers", that cover the most interesting markets in the Black Sea region, Europe and the world;
•	A Daily Analysis and a Morning Review directly sent to their email box, in which our subscribers are the first to learn in brief what happened on the grain markets the day before;
•	Daily reports for ships under loading, arriving and raiding at Romanian ports on the Black Sea and the Danube - Constanța port, Brăila, Galați, Calafat, Corabia, through which can be monitored the trade flows of interest - by types of crops, exporters, ports, destinations, etc. Complete statistics on exports of all cereals and oilseeds for subscribers with Lineup access, showing details of trade flows for past crop years.
•	A Balance Section that gives opportunity to monitor the fundamental indicators of the main crops in Romania. The service is unique in terms of functionality and reflects in real time production, planted and harvested acreage, yields, exports and domestic consumption and carry over.

